<link href="adcp.css" rel="stylesheet"><entry><xh5>wring one’s hands • wring someone’s hand</xh5><p> <i>wring one’s hands</i>—1. squeeze one’s hands together to express despair, sorrow, etc.: His face was pale, and he stared at his feet while <u>wringing his hands</u> nervously. 2. be very worried or upset about smth.: Our President is all day in security sessions, briefings, debriefings, staying up all night <u>wringing his hands</u> over this whole mess.</p><p><i>wring someone’s hand—</i>shake hands with a person showing more emotion than in the usual handshake: He shook hands with Tom, <u>wringing his hand</u> harder than he knew.</p> </entry>
